        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 26 at 7:46PM CDT until June 26 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 746 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 8 miles west of Ware to 13 miles north of Romero,
moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

These severe thunderstorms will remain over mainly rural areas of
southwestern Dallam and northwestern Hartley Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
